.TH LPF 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf \- PF\-style control plane for Linux networking
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf <command> [arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
lpf is an OCaml\-first control plane for readable Linux firewall and routing policy.
It compiles typed policy into nftables, policy routing, tc, conntrack, and logging plans.
Remote\-safe apply, rollback, explainability, policy tests, generated man pages, and kernel compatibility validation are core requirements.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
lpf check
parse and validate policy without touching the host
.TP
lpf fmt
format policy files deterministically
.TP
lpf plan
compile policy to a typed backend change plan
.TP
lpf diff
show the delta between current host state and a plan
.TP
lpf apply
apply a plan with confirmation and rollback support
.TP
lpf confirm
confirm a pending guarded apply
.TP
lpf rollback
restore a previous known\-good policy state
.TP
lpf explain
explain why a hypothetical packet passes or drops
.TP
lpf test
run policy assertion fixtures
.TP
lpf table
manage dynamic policy tables
.TP
lpf state
inspect or modify conntrack state
.TP
lpf rules
show or diff generated backend rules
.TP
lpf history
show policy apply history and rollback points
.TP
lpf e2e
run Firecracker guest end\-to\-end networking scenarios
.TP
lpf man
generate, check, or install man pages
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Run lpf check and lpf plan before applying host changes.
Use guarded apply with an explicit confirmation window for remote hosts.
Keep rollback evidence server\-side; never rely on browser\-only state.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf.conf(5), lpf\-policy\-tests(5), lpf\-apply(8), lpf\-man(8)
